26/12/2007
BAGHDAD, Iraq/TIRANA, Albania -- Albanian President Bamir Topi -- accompanied by Defence Minister Fatmir Mediu and the Chief of General Staff Lieutenant General Luan Hoxha -- paid a surprise visit to Iraq on Sunday (December 23rd). The group visited the Albanian contingent in Mosul and awarded the 71 Albanian troops, who are stationed at a US Air Force base, with the Golden Eagle medal for their "courage, bravery and exceptional professionalism". Topi also met with Iraqi Prime Minister Nuri al-Maliki and the commander of the multinational force in Iraq, US General David Petraeus. The Albanian president expressed his country's readiness to contribute more troops to Iraq. (Xinhua - 25/12/07; MIA, Albanian president website - 23/12/07)
